    "body": "This should resolve the bug mentioned in [this comment](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/pull/31311#issuecomment-2511024970).\r\n\r\nThe reproduction method is to open a relatively large file (so the server needs some time to process the request), and then immediately execute `:bd`. Once the request is completed, the handler will obtain the bufstate of a buffer already unloaded.\r\n\r\nShould this fix be applied at a lower level, that is, should all pending requests of the client attached to the buffer be immediately canceled after the buffer is unloaded?",
    "closed_at": null,
    "comment_data": [],
    "comment_regular_data": [
        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "> Should this fix be applied at a lower level, that is, should all pending requests of the client attached to the buffer be immediately canceled after the buffer is unloaded?\r\n\r\nYeah, I personally think that this cancellation should happen for all pending requests and not only for folding ranges.",
